        "title": "See also"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The Kaiser window is defined as"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "formulas": [
              "w(n) = I_0\\left( \\beta \\sqrt{1-\\frac{4n^2}{(M-1)^2}} \\right)/I_0(\\beta)"
            ],
            "type": "math_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "with"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "formulas": [
              "\\quad -\\frac{M-1}{2} \\leq n \\leq \\frac{M-1}{2},"
            ],
            "type": "math_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "where "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "I_0"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is the modified zeroth-order Bessel function."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The Kaiser was named for Jim Kaiser, who discovered a simple\napproximation to the DPSS window based on Bessel functions.  The Kaiser\nwindow is a very good approximation to the Digital Prolate Spheroidal\nSequence, or Slepian window, which is the transform which maximizes the\nenergy in the main lobe of the window relative to total energy."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The Kaiser can approximate many other windows by varying the beta\nparameter."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "raw_kind": "table",
            "raw_text": "\n\n\n\nbeta\n\nWindow shape\n\n0\n\nRectangular\n\n5\n\nSimilar to a Hamming\n\n6\n\nSimilar to a Hanning\n\n8.6\n\nSimilar to a Blackman",
            "type": "raw_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "A beta value of 14 is probably a good starting point. Note that as beta\ngets large, the window narrows, and so the number of samples needs to be\nlarge enough to sample the increasingly narrow spike, otherwise NaNs will\nget returned."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Most references to the Kaiser window come from the signal processing\nliterature, where it is used as one of many windowing functions for\nsmoothing values.  It is also known as an apodization (which means\n\"removing the foot\", i.e. smoothing discontinuities at the beginning\nand end of the sampled signal) or tapering function."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Notes"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "1\n\nJ. F. Kaiser, \"Digital Filters\" - Ch 7 in \"Systems analysis by\ndigital computer\", Editors: F.F. Kuo and J.F. Kaiser, p 218-285.\nJohn Wiley and Sons, New York, (1966).",
            "type": "raw_block"
          },
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "2\n\nE.R. Kanasewich, \"Time Sequence Analysis in Geophysics\", The\nUniversity of Alberta Press, 1975, pp. 177-178.",
            "type": "raw_block"
          },
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "3\n\nWikipedia, \"Window function\",\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Window_function",
            "type": "raw_block"
          }
        ],
        "title": "References"
      },
